Write a program to find the average of a 1-D array.

Program:

#include<stdio.h>
int main ()
{
    int n,i,sum=0,average;
    printf("Enter the size of array:");
    scanf("%d",&n);
    int a[n];
    printf("The elements of array are:");
    for(i =0;i<n;i++)
    {
        scanf("%d",&a[i]);
    }
    for(i =0;i<n;i++)
    {
        printf("\nThe elements are: %d",a[i]);
    }
    for(i =0;i<=n;i++)
    {
        sum = sum+i;
    }
    printf("\nThe sum of elements in an array is %d",sum);
    average = sum/n;
    printf("\nThe average of elements in an array is %d",average);
    return 0;
}

Output:
Enter the size of array:5

The elements of array are:1 2 3 4 5

The elements are: 1
The elements are: 2
The elements are: 3
The elements are: 4
The elements are: 5
The sum of elements in an array is 15
The average of elements in an array is 3
